node.text: 📌 Volcanic lava can flow at speeds up to 60 mph, melting everything in its path. Nature is unstoppable!🌋

“I spotted this flow exiting a lava tube a couple of days ago. I found the simplicity and symmetry of it very soothing. It almost looks like an ice cream dispenser. #iceland

📷 It was surprisingly challenging to capture this due to the massive RF interference. I haven’t experienced such interference before at an eruption and haven’t since. I suspect the cause was not only the large number of drones in the air but also the geomagnetic activity at the time. While I had no way to measure the temperature of the lava at the time, this could also have contributed to the poor, and often disconnecting signal.” - Jeroen Van Nieuwenhove
cc: @jvn.photo
